Remove the seeds and white ribs from the @red bell pepper{1}(seeds removed and thinly sliced). Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Thinly slice half the @jalapeño{1}(thinly sliced) into rounds. Mince the remaining jalapeño, removing the ribs and seeds if you prefer less heat. Zest and halve the @lime{1}, then cut one half into wedges. Thinly slice the @chicken breasts{12%ounce} into strips.

> Thoroughly wash hands and surfaces after handling the jalapeno. The heat is transferable and can burn more than your throat.

== Quick-Pickled Jalapeno ==

Place the jalapeno rounds in a #small bowl{} and toss with the juice of half the lime.

== Fajita Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add the onions and red bell pepper to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{7-8%minutes}, until softened and slightly caramelized. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

== Lime Crema ==

In a small bowl, stir together the @sour cream{2%ounce}, lime zest, and a squeeze of lime. Add 2-3 tablespoons water to thin to a dressing-like consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Chicken Fajitas ==

Add the minced jalapeno to the pan with the fajita veggies. Cook, tossing, for about ~{1%minute}, until fragrant. Add the chicken and @Southwest Spice Blend{1%teaspoon} to the pan and cook, tossing, for ~{4-5%minutes}, until the chicken is cooked through. Season with salt and pepper.

== Cheesy Tortillas ==

While the chicken cooks, lay the @flour tortilla{6} in a single layer on a #baking sheet{}. Sprinkle each tortilla with a bit of @cheddar cheese{2%ounce} and place in the oven for about ~{1-2%minutes}, until melted.

> Keep an eye on these! They can burn quickly.

== Assembly ==

Place the chicken mixture inside the cheesy tortillas. Top with the lime crema and quick-pickled jalapeno. Serve with a wedge of lime and enjoy!